---
description: vCloudTech Architecture Rules
alwaysApply: true
---

# Project Architecture

This project uses the Next.js App Router architecture.

Always follow the existing folder structure and project conventions.

Never introduce a different architecture unless explicitly requested.

---

# Existing Before New

Before creating:

- Page
- Layout
- Component
- Hook
- Utility
- CSS file

Search the project first.

Reuse existing implementations whenever possible.

Do not duplicate functionality.

---

# Marketing Pages

Marketing pages follow existing shared patterns.

Before creating a new Hero, CTA, Card or Section:

- Check existing marketing components.
- Extend existing components if appropriate.
- Only create a new component when reuse is not practical.

---

# Content

Marketing copy belongs inside:

lib/marketing/

Never hardcode large text inside React components.

---

# Images

Always use the project's existing asset system.

Prefer existing public asset helpers.

Do not hardcode asset paths if a helper already exists.

---

# Styling

Follow the project's existing styling strategy.

Reuse existing CSS.

Reuse Tailwind utilities.

Reuse design tokens.

Do not introduce another styling framework.

---

# Components

Keep components focused.

Avoid components larger than necessary.

Extract reusable pieces only after duplication exists.

---

# Imports

Follow existing import style.

Prefer project aliases over deep relative imports.

---

# File Changes

Touch only the files required.

Avoid unrelated refactoring.

Never rename files unless requested.

---

# Before Completion

Before completing work verify:

- Existing architecture preserved
- Existing design system respected
- Existing reusable components considered
- No duplicated logic introduced